CoverCurves

CoverCurves([ ...])

Description:
Generic cover curves functionality.CoverCurves has two modi:
- Cover planar curve: Create a complex set of curves making up a closed loop. CoverCurves will create a surface that fits the loop
- Skinning with guide curves: Create a set of skinning curves (may be of arbitrary complexity, but G1. Create simple Guide Curves that pass through all the skinning curves (defines the internal topology + bounding curve)
The skinning curves may not intersect.
The simple Guide Curves may not intersect.

The curves are analyzed internally, so the order which they are passed to CoverCurves is arbitrary.

CoverCurves

CoverCurves(Array)

Description:
Generic cover curves functionality.CoverCurves has two modi:
- Cover planar curve: Create a complex set of curves making up a closed loop. CoverCurves will create a surface that fits the loop
- Skinning with guide curves: Create a set of skinning curves (may be of arbitrary complexity, but G1. Create simple Guide Curves that pass through all the skinning curves (defines the internal topology + bounding curve)
The skinning curves may not intersect.
The simple Guide Curves may not intersect.

The curves are analyzed internally, so the order which they are passed to CoverCurves is arbitrary.

CreateHoleFromProfile

CreateHoleFromProfile(ProfileRR profileCurve, Point anchorPoint, LengthVector3d normalVector, Angle rotationAngle)

Description:
Creates a hole from a rounded rectangle 2d-profile curve.
Example of use:
Create Hole From Profile
Hole1 = CreateHoleFromProfile(profileCurve,anchorPoint,normalVector,rotationAngle,translationVector);
AchorPoint is the point of the model, where the 2d-profile-center will be placed on. The profile center is the cog of its control polygon.
NormalVector is the normal vector at the anchor-point.
RotationAngle is the angle of rotation of the 2d-profile around the normal vector.
TranslationVector is a vector of 2d-translation of the 2d-profile

mpIncludeUnusedProperties

Preference mpIncludeUnusedProperties()

Description:
Global preference for includeing unused properties to be included in FEM meshSetting this value to true will let the mesher include unused section, material and thickness properties in FEM mesh. Useful for ensuring better consistency between different model variants.

mpMeshDensityRounded

Preference mpMeshDensityRounded()

Description:
Global preference for interpretation of mesh densitySetting this value changes (globally) the interpretation of the mesh density set on each part. The default value of the parameter is "false".

Mesh density is among other things used to calculate the number of elements along any given edge, i.e. number_of_elements = edge_length/mesh_density

Obviously, the division is a floating point number that must be rounded up or down to yield an integer value (an edge cannot have 3.14 number of elements for example).

  • Setting mpMeshDensityRounded to true will imply using normal rounding rules (e.g. 3.14 is rounded to 3 while 3.54 is rounded to 4).
  • Setting mpMeshDensityRounded to false will always result in rounding up (i.e. both 3.14 and 3.54 results in 4 elements along the edge).

mpPreferLinearDependencies

Preference mpPreferLinearDependencies()

Description:
Global preference for creating linear dependencies instead of very stiff springs for ppcs

mpPreferPointMassAsNodeMass

Preference mpPreferPointMassAsNodeMass()

Description:
Global preference for representing point masses as node masses (not elements) in FEM mesh

mpPreferRectangularMesh
